✨ TaskFlow - A Modern Task Management Board
🚀 Description
TaskFlow is a clean, intuitive, and feature-rich web application designed to help you organize your workflow with ease. It features a beautiful, glassy interface with a full drag-and-drop system, allowing you to seamlessly move tasks between "To Do," "In Progress," and "Done" columns. The application is built with vanilla HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, and it uses your browser's local storage to save your tasks, ensuring they persist even after you close the tab.

🌟 Features
📝 Add & Edit Tasks: Quickly add new tasks or edit existing ones through a clean, user-friendly modal.

↔️ Drag & Drop: Effortlessly move tasks across different columns to update their status.

🎨 Priority Levels: Assign 'Low', 'Medium', or 'High' priority to tasks, indicated by a colored border.

📅 Due Dates: Add due dates to your tasks to keep track of deadlines.

🔍 Filter Tasks: Instantly filter your board to view tasks of a specific priority.

🌙 Light & Dark Themes: Toggle between a light and dark theme for comfortable viewing in any environment.

🗑️ Delete & Clear: Remove individual tasks or clear all completed tasks with a single click.

💾 Persistent Storage: Your task board is automatically saved to your browser's local storage.

📱 Responsive Design: The layout is fully responsive and works beautifully on desktops, tablets, and mobile devices.

💻 Technologies Used
HTML5: For the structure and content of the application.

CSS3: For custom styling, animations, and the glassy UI effects.

JavaScript (ES6+): For all interactive functionality, state management, and DOM manipulation.

Font Awesome: For modern and clean icons used throughout the application.

Google Fonts: For the 'Inter' font family to ensure crisp, readable typography.

🚀 How to Use
Getting started with TaskFlow is simple:

Clone or Download: Get a local copy of the project files (index.html, style.css, script.js).

Open the File: Open the index.html file in any modern web browser (like Google Chrome, Firefox, or Safari).

Start Organizing: That's it! You can begin adding and managing your tasks immediately.

